/release/rl773883393/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Colombia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl35685889/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (New Zealand)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl69240321/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Peru)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Argentina, Australia, and Bolivia on January 3, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl924878337/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Argentina)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl689997313/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Australia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl740328961/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Bolivia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Brazil, Central America, and Uruguay on January 4, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl757106177/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Brazil)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl539002369/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Central America)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl1981842945/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Uruguay)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Egypt on January 9, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl404784641/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Egypt)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Serbia and Montenegro on January 10, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2082506241/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Serbia and Montenegro)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Poland on January 11, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl102794753/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Poland)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> the Philippines on January 16, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl86017537/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Philippines)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Croatia and Slovakia on January 17, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl522225153/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Croatia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl1881179649/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Slovakia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> India, Indonesia, and Italy on January 18, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl304121345/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (India)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl287344129/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Indonesia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl337675777/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Italy)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> the Dominican Republic on January 24, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl622888449/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Dominican Republic)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Denmark and Sweden on February 1, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl606111233/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Denmark)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2099283457/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Sweden)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> the Netherlands on February 6, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl488670721/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Netherlands)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Finland and Norway on February 8, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl438339073/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Finland)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl18908673/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Norway)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Slovenia on February 14, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2132837889/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Slovenia)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> Vietnam on March 14, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl1797293569/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Vietnam)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> and Japan on September 13, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl388007425/weekend/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (Japan)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical reviews ===\nMonths before its release, bloggers predicted ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' to be terrible due to the involvement of the director of ''[[Garfield: A Tail of Two Kitties]]'' (2006);<ref name = \"vespemar\">{{cite web|last=Vespe|first=Eric|date=March 8, 2007|url=http://legacy.aintitcool.com/node/31805|title=Oh God, Jason Lee why? ALVIN AND THE CHIPMUNKS movie from the mind-blowing talents behind the GARFIELD movie sequel?!? |website=[[Ain't It Cool News]]|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"Slashposter\">{{cite web|last=Sciretta|first=Peter|date=July 3, 2007|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-movie-poster/|title=Alvin and The Chipmunks Movie Poster|work=[[/Film]]|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref> the writers of the [[Ice Age (franchise)|''Ice Age'' films]], ''[[Robots (2005 film)|Robots]]'' (2005) and ''[[Big Momma's House 2]]'' (2006);<ref name = \"Slashposter\"/> and the poor quality of previous live-action adaptations of old cartoons.<ref name = \"vespemar\"/>\n\n''[[Rotten Tomatoes]]'' reported that \"critics say this may be the weakest vehicle for the helium-voiced rodents yet,\" elaborating, \"the pundits say despite a few laughs, this is pretty bland stuff: dated, weakly constructed, and lacking in three-dimensional characters of the human or CGI variety.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Ryan|first=Tim|date=December 13, 2007|url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/Critical-Consensus-I-Am-Legend-All-Over-the-Map-Chipmunks-Hits-Sour-Note/|title=Critical Consensus: ''I Am Legend'' All Over the Map, ''Chipmunks'' Hits Sour Note|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> As of November 2016, the film holds a score of 28% of 109 critical reviews being fresh,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1184827-alvin_and_the_chipmunks/| title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (2007) |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=November 23, 2016}}</ref> and has a [[standard score|normalized]] rating of 39/100 based on 23 professional reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/film/titles/alvinandthechipmunks?q=alvin%20and%20the%20chipmunks |title=Alvin and the Chipmunks |publisher=Metacritic |accessdate=December 25, 2009}}</ref> However, it had a far more favorable audience reception, as indicated by its [[CinemaScore]] grade of an A.<ref>{{cite web |title= CinemaScore |url= https://www.cinemascore.com/publicsearch/index/title/ |website= [[CinemaScore]] |access-date= October 20, 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180206073531/https://www.cinemascore.com/publicsearch/index/title/ |archive-date= February 6, 2018 |url-status= dead }}</ref> ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' is an \"occasionally rancid but mostly just dull film that isn\u2019t as excruciating as ''[[Garfield: The Movie]]'',\" concluded ''[[Creative Loafing]]'';<ref>{{cite web|last=Brunson|first=Matt|date=December 19, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071226032054/http://charlotte.creativeloafing.com/gyrobase/pregnant_with_possibility/Content?oid=237233|archivedate=December 26, 2007|url=http://charlotte.creativeloafing.com/gyrobase/pregnant_with_possibility/Content?oid=237233|title=Pregnant with Possibility|work=[[Creative Loafing]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> and ''[[Total Film]]'' summarized it consists of \"trite family values, mediocre CGI and a shallow anti-exploitation message.\"<ref name = \"Totalfilm\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071221054234/http://www.totalfilm.com/cinema_reviews/films_out_this_week/alvin_and_the_chipmunks|archivedate=December 21, 2007|url=http://www.totalfilm.com/cinema_reviews/films_out_this_week/alvin_and_the_chipmunks|title=Alvin And The Chipmunks \u2013 Film Review|date=December 21, 2007|work=[[Total Film]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> ''[[News & Review]]'' summarized ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' as \"disposable junk that\u2019ll probably be forgotten in a month,\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lane|first=Jim|date=December 13, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171209101148/https://www.newsreview.com/sacramento/alvin-the-chipmunks/content?oid=606264|archivedate=December 9, 2017|url=https://www.newsreview.com/sacramento/alvin-the-chipmunks/content?oid=606264|title=''Alvin and the Chipmunks''|work=[[News & Review]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> but [[Philip French]] wrote that \"kids will love it and I found it tolerable.\"<ref>{{cite web|authorlink=Phillip French|last=French|first=Phillip|date=December 23, 2007|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2007/dec/23/features.review87|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[The Observer]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nCritics called its plot \"predictable,\"<ref name = \"Azzcentral\"/><ref name = \"TorontoStar\">{{cite web|last=Walker|first=Susan|date=December 14, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130060303/https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2007/12/14/alvin_and_the_chipmunks_blast_from_past.html|archivedate=November 30, 2017|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2007/12/14/alvin_and_the_chipmunks_blast_from_past.html|title='Alvin and the Chipmunks': Blast from past|work=[[Toronto Star]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> \"pencil-thin,\"<ref name = \"Totalfilm\"/> \"over-familiar,\"<ref name = \"Empire\"/> \"paper-thin,\"<ref name = \"NYpost\">{{cite web|last=Lumenick|first=Lou|date=December 14, 2007|url=https://nypost.com/2007/12/14/updated-alvin-a-gyp-munk/|title=Updated Alvin a Gyp-munk|work=[[New York Post]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> \"strictly by-the-numbers,\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Savlov|first=Marc|date=December 14, 2007|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/events/film/2007-12-14/570393/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[The Austin Chronicle]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> \"airplane fodder,\"<ref name = \"NYTrev\"/> and in \"formulaic [[Disney Channel]] territory.\"<ref name = \"WadeMaj\"/> Jeff Vice wrote, \"Even at a relatively scant 92 minutes, the film feels a little padded. And again, relying on lowest common-denominator humor is a sure sign of desperation on the part of the three credited screenwriters.\"<ref name = \"Desertnews\"/> Explained the ''[[Daily Mirror]]'', \"things like storyline and character development are barely in evidence with the whole point of the movie being to keep the chipmunks on screen.\"<ref name = \"mirror\"/> The most common censure was the film's satire on commercialism, which was hypocritical due to being bombarded with popular brands, including the chipmunks themselves.<ref name = \"ChicagoReader\"/><ref name = \"LAWeekly\">{{cite web|url=https://www.laweekly.com/movie-reviews-alvin-and-the-chipmunks-look-the-perfect-holiday/|title=Movie Reviews: Alvin and the Chipmunks, Look, The Perfect Holiday|work=[[LA Weekly]]|date=December 12, 2007|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"NYpost\"/><ref name = \"sfgate\">{{cite web|last=Hartlaub|first=Peter|date=December 14, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111114084711/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2007/12/14/DDGCTR30V.DTL&type=movies|archivedate=November 14, 2011|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2007/12/14/DDGCTR30V.DTL&type=movies|title=Review: 'Alvin and the Chipmunks' get a 21st century update|work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"Timeout\">{{cite web|url=https://www.timeout.com/london/film/alvin-and-the-chipmunks|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out London]]|date=December 17, 2007|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Fox|first=Ken|date=May 18, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080407050805/http://www.tvguide.com/movies/alvin-chipmunks/review/291755|archivedate=April 7, 2008|url=http://www.tvguide.com/movies/alvin-chipmunks/review/291755|title=\nAlvin And The Chipmunks|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"Telegraph\">{{cite web|last=Robey|first=Tim|date=December 21, 2007|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/filmreviews/3670069/Film-reviews-St-Trinians-Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-and-A-Comedy-of-Power.html|title=Film reviews: St Trinian's, Alvin and the Chipmunks and A Comedy of Power|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"Empire\">{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Anna|date=July 4, 2007|url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/alvin-chipmunks-review/|title=Alvin And The Chipmunks Review|work=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> Explained Burr, the film's message \"is torn between the glitz that sells and the homilies that endure.\"<ref name = \"Bostongl\">{{cite web|last=Burr|first=Ty|date=December 14, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080424054217/http://www.boston.com/movies/display?display=movie&id=10081|archivedate=April 24, 2008|url=http://www.boston.com/movies/display?display=movie&id=10081|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Slant Magazine]]'', however, did somewhat enjoy ''Alvin of the Chipmunks'' for being \"intermittently cute,\" and \"you may even appreciate it as a music-industry satire;\"<ref name = \"Slant\">{{cite web|last=Gonzalez|first=Ed|date=December 9, 2007|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/film/alvin-and-the-chipmunks/|title=Review: ''Alvin and the Chipmunks''|work=[[Slant Magazine]]|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> and ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' writer Stephen Cole called its non-musical segments \"pretty funny and absolutely adult-friendly\" while more annoyed by the chipmunks singing.<ref name = \"Globeandmail\">{{cite web|last=Cole|first=Stephen|date=December 14, 2007|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/funny-till-the-munks-get-funky/article726649/|title=Funny, till the 'munks get funky|work=[[The Globe and Mail]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> The ''[[Toronto Star]]'' also thought the unoriginal plot was made up for by endless \"entertaining antics,\"<ref name = \"TorontoStar\"/> and a ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' critic found \"a few funny moments\" in the mostly \"soulless\" content, such as a joke making fun of lip-syncing in live performances.<ref name = \"sfgate\"/> Anna Smith also highlighted its \"cartoonish visual comedy,\" and \"the \u2019munks themselves are pretty cute: their nimbly choreographed version of Funky Town is a hoot, and chubby Theodore is bound to elicit \u201caahhs\u201d as he snuggles up to Dave after having nightmares.\"<ref name = \"Empire\"/> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' was also favorable towards the film's \"sweetness.\"<ref name = \"LATimes\"/>\n[[File:DavidCross2007.jpg|thumb|Several film reviewers praised Cross' performance as the villain.]]\nExplained Ty Burr, \"the script leans heavily on the pranks and big-eyed cuteness of the li'l guys and leaves the live actors with unfunny dialogue and nothing to do.\"<ref name = \"Bostongl\"/> According to ''[[The New York Times]]'', \"its animated protagonists are egregiously eclipsed by the live-action characters.\"<ref name = \"NYTrev\"/> ''[[Chicago Reader]]'' criticized the \"cardboard\" characters of David Seville and Ian Hawke.<ref name = \"ChicagoReader\"/> Some critics disliked Lee's under-acting,<ref name = \"Variety\"/><ref name = \"AVclub\"/><ref name = \"Desertnews\">{{cite web|last=Vice|first=Jeff|date=December 13, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117215911/https://www.deseretnews.com/article/700004757/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks.html|archivedate=January 17, 2018|url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/700004757/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks.html|title=Film review: Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Deseret News]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hunter|first=Stephen|date=December 14, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171209101144/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/12/13/AR2007121300753.html|archivedate=December 9, 2017|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/12/13/AR2007121300753.html|title=Singing the Same Old Song|work=[[The Washington Post]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> particularly his underwhelming yelling of the word \"Alvin!\"<ref name = \"Premiere\">{{cite web|last=Grant|first=Andrew|date=December 13, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080915122449/http://www.premiere.com/moviereviews/4318/alvin-and-the-chipmunks.html|archivedate=September 15, 2008|url=http://www.premiere.com/moviereviews/4318/alvin-and-the-chipmunks.html|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Premiere (magazine)|Premiere]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"LAWeekly\"/><ref name = \"EWreview\">{{cite web|last=Willman|first=Chris|date=April 4, 2008|url=https://ew.com/article/2008/04/04/alvin-and-chipmunks-2/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"LATimes\">{{cite web|last=Ordona|first=Michael|date=December 14, 2007|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2007-dec-14-et-chipmunks14-story.html|title='Chipmunks' hits kid-friendly note|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> In ''[[Premiere (magazine)|Premiere]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s view, \"Jason Lee makes for a sympathetic Dave, yet there's an almost somnambulistic quality to his performance;\"<ref name = \"Premiere\">{{cite web|last=Grant|first=Andrew|date=December 13, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080915122449/http://www.premiere.com/moviereviews/4318/alvin-and-the-chipmunks.html|archivedate=September 15, 2008|url=http://www.premiere.com/moviereviews/4318/alvin-and-the-chipmunks.html|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Premiere (magazine)|Premiere]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> and Vice wrote that Lee's \"rather 'cartoony' acting style here leaves a lot to be desired.\"<ref name = \"Desertnews\"/> However, Lee's acting did have some supporters for working as a likable protagonist,<ref name = \"mirror\"/><ref name = \"Empire\"/><ref name = \"Hollywoodreporter\">{{cite web|last=Scheck|first=Frank|date=December 13, 2007|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/alvin-chipmunks-158437|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> such as ''[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]'', a source that thought his \"wry approach lends an edge to some of the script\u2019s wittier moments.\"<ref name = \"Timeout\"/> Some reviewers praised Cross' performance,<ref name = \"EWreview\"/><ref name = \"NYTrev\">{{cite web|last=Webster|first=Andy|date=December 14, 2007|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/14/movies/14chip.html|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Weitzman|first=Elizabeth|date=June 3, 2008|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/chipmunks-drive-rodent-rage-article-1.272123|title='Chipmunks' drive us to rodent rage|work=[[New York Daily News]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"sfgate\"/><ref name = \"mirror\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071224181331/http://www.mirror.co.uk/showbiz/entertainment/movies/2007/12/21/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-89520-20260445/|archivedate=December 24, 2007|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/showbiz/entertainment/movies/2007/12/21/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-89520-20260445/|title=Alvin And The Chipmunks|date=December 21, 2007|work=[[Daily Mirror]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"Variety\">{{cite web|last=Leydon|first=Joe|date=December 13, 2007|url=https://variety.com/2007/film/markets-festivals/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-2-1200553983/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=December 13, 2011}}</ref> such as Bill Goodykoontz of ''[[The Arizona Republic]]'' who called the villain the highlight of the film: \"Cross is hilarious in everything he does, but he's surprisingly effective in a kids comedy. His villainy is so broad that it's never really scary, and he's so funny that you never tire of seeing him on-screen.\"<ref name = \"Azzcentral\">{{cite web|last=Goodykoontz|first=Bill|date=December 13, 2007|url=http://archive.azcentral.com/ent/movies/articles/2007/12/13/20071213alvin1214.html|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[The Arizona Republic]]|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> However, one reviewer, Tim Robey, admitted to being annoyed by Cross in the film.<ref name = \"Telegraph\"/> ''Premiere'' called Richardson \"sufficiently adorable and winsome, though the film's purity makes it difficult to imagine any sort of romantic entanglement.\"<ref name = \"Premiere\"/> Wrote [[Roger Ebert]], \"Jason Lee and David Cross manfully play roles that require them, as actors, to relate with empty space that would later be filled with CGI.\"<ref name = \"Ebert\">{{cite web|authorlink=Roger Ebert|last=Ebert|first=Roger|date=December 13, 2007|url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-2007|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|website=[[RogerEbert.com]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAs stated in a review from ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'', \"the values and the CGI are good.\"<ref name = \"Phila\">{{cite web|last=Rickey|first=Carrie|date=December 14, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219073958/http://www.philly.com/inquirer/columnists/carrie_rickey/20071214_Please__Alvin__dont_be_so_darned_nice.html|archivedate=December 19, 2007|url=http://www.philly.com/inquirer/columnists/carrie_rickey/20071214_Please__Alvin__dont_be_so_darned_nice.html|title=Please, Alvin, don't be so darned nice|work=[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Some critics praised the chipmunk protagonists,<ref name = \"ChicagoReader\">{{cite web|last=Gronvall |first=Andrea|date=December 20, 2007 |title=Alvin and the Chipmunks |work=[[Chicago Reader]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071218194056/http://onfilm.chicagoreader.com/movies/briefs/32583_ALVIN_AND_CHIPMUNKS.html|archivedate=December 18, 2007|url=http://onfilm.chicagoreader.com/movies/briefs/32583_ALVIN_AND_CHIPMUNKS.html|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name = \"LAWeekly\"/> Vice writing they were \"integrated pretty well into the live-action elements.\"<ref name = \"Desertnews\"/> ''The A.V. Club'', however, stated \"the manic Chipmunks wear out their welcome pretty quickly,\"<ref name = \"AVclub\">{{cite web|last=Phipps|first=Keith|date=December 12, 2007|url=https://film.avclub.com/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-1798203527|title=Alvin And The Chipmunks|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> some critics described the animation as \"too bland\"<ref name = \"EWreview\"/> and \"adequate yet underwhelming,\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Bushell|first=Laura|date=December 21, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201015517/http://www.bbc.co.uk/films/2007/12/17/alvin_and_the_chipmunks_2007_review.shtml|archivedate=December 1, 2017|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/films/2007/12/17/alvin_and_the_chipmunks_2007_review.shtml|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (2007)|website=[[BBC]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref> and ''Slant Magazine'' criticized the \"static\" compositing of CGI animals into live-action shots.<ref name = \"Slant\"/> Cole also commented on the shot composition, \"you've got regulation-height dancers and musicians backing a singing group the size of kids' mittens.\"<ref name = \"Globeandmail\"/> \"As rendered here by the average-looking CGI effects, the characters are underwhelming in their appeal, lacking the charm of their previous animated incarnations,\" summarized ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]''.<ref name = \"Hollywoodreporter\"/> Some reviewers, including Ebert, also panned the lack of distinction between the chipmunks.<ref name = \"Ebert\"/><ref name = \"Phila\"/> However, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' thought there was a \"persuasive interaction of human and digital co-stars.\"<ref name = \"Variety\"/> \n\nCritic Roger Moore praised ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' for the interactions between David Seville and the chipmunks, and references to previous ''Alvin'' media.<ref name = \"orlSentinel\">{{cite web|last=Moore|first=Roger|date=December 14, 2007|url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/os-xpm-2007-12-14-alvin-story.html|title=Yesterday's charm, today's wit meld nicely in 'Chipmunks'|work=[[Orlando Sentinel]]|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Wade Major appreciated its \"momentary burst of nostalgia\" from the presentation of how \"[[Christmas Don't Be Late]]\" was created.<ref name = \"WadeMaj\">{{cite web|last=Major|first=Wade|date=December 13, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071218133913/http://boxoffice.com/reviews/2007/12/alvin-and-the-chipmunks.php|archivedate=December 18, 2007|url=http://boxoffice.com/reviews/2007/12/alvin-and-the-chipmunks.php|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks|work=[[Boxoffice Pro|Boxoffice]]|accessdate=December 23, 2019}}</ref> ''CinemaBlend'' was very favorable, calling it \"easily their best [film], getting back to where it all began: a down on his luck musician and three singing chipmunks.\"<ref name = \"CinemaBlend\">{{cite web|last=Gwin|first=Scott|year=2007|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/reviews/Alvin-and-The-Chipmunks-2787.html|title=Alvin and The Chipmunks|website=CinemaBlend|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Goodykoontz opined that \"the songs are catchy, and some of the videos and marketing that Ian devises to sell more product are funny (or at least cute). They don't quite rise to the level of corporate satire, but this isn't really the audience for that, anyway.\"<ref name = \"Azzcentral\"/> ''Premiere'' called it unique from other family films for being \"sweet, innocent fare that's strictly for the kiddies,\" elaborating, \"the film contains a healthy dose of uplifting lessons on what it means to be a family. At times funny, and even occasionally witty, Alvin and the Chipmunks is a lively, entertaining romp that will certainly bring smiles to the young ones this holiday season.\"<ref name = \"Premiere\"/>\n\n==== Response towards Cross ====\n[[File:Patton Oswalt-Rififi-07-10-2007-2.jpg|thumb|left|Negative fan responses as well as a joke about Cross' involvement in ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' made in a blog by [[Patton Oswalt]] ''(pictured)'' influenced Cross to write on his blog about why he worked on the film.]]\nCross' appearance in ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' was negatively received by fans of the comedian, ''[[The New York Observer]]'' reporting blog comments that called him a \"smug, condescending asshole\" and \"a huge prick.\"<ref name = \"Observer\">{{cite web|last=Haber|first=Matt|date=January 10, 2008|url=https://observer.com/2008/01/in-defense-of-david-cross/|title=In Defense of David Cross|work=[[The New York Observer]]|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref> On December 10, 2007, comedian [[Patton Oswalt]] published a writing on his [[MySpace]] blog titled \"Godawful/Thank God,\" where he revealed he and [[Brian Posehn]] were approached for the part of Ian for ''Alvin and the Chipmunks''; he made the following remark in the post: \"We both threw the script across the room in disgust. David Cross caught it.\"<ref name = \"Oswalt\">{{cite web|authorlink=Patton Oswalt|last=Oswalt|first=Patton|date=January 2, 2008|url=https://film.avclub.com/patton-oswalt-responds-1798213018|title=Patton Oswalt Responds|work=The A.V. Club|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> \n\nAll of this prompted Cross to publicly discuss his involvement with the film on his website ''The Bob and Davider'' on December 31, 2007.<ref name = \"Crossblog\">{{cite web|authorlink=David Cross|last=Cross|first=David|date=December 31, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080103174313/http://www.bobanddavid.com/2007/12/allllllviiiiin.html|url=http://www.bobanddavid.com/2007/12/allllllviiiiin.html|archivedate=January 3, 2008|title=Allllllviiiiin!|website=The Bob and Davider|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> He explained that he actually was offered the role before the casting team approached Oswalt and Posehn, but rejected. He got the offer again after six months of failing to find acting work and having a [[down payment]] on a cottage in the middle of [[Sullivan County, New York]] due; this time, he accepted the role out of desperation.<ref name = \"Crossblog\"/> He also admitted in the post he never saw the film, and hoped that his post \"hopefully lessens some of the sense that I'm some kind of whore sell-out who doesn't care about anything but making money.\"<ref name = \"Crossblog\"/> The post only garnered more bad comments on blog stories about it: a ''[[Gawker|Defamer]]'' reader commented that it was \"the shittiest fucking defense since the [[Nuremberg trials]],\" an ''A.V. Club'' user stated that \"he's digging his own grave, professionally,\" and a ''[[Stereogum]]'' reader thought he \"wouldn\u2019t mind if [Cross] dies.\"<ref name = \"Observer\"/> \n\nOswalt responded to the post via ''The A.V. Club'' on January 2, 2008. He revealed that the comment towards Cross was nothing more than a \"snide, private in-joke between us\" that referenced a comment Cross made at a party in New York in March 2006; Cross had just received the script for ''[[Failure to Launch]]'' and stated, \"Man, they sent me that script, and I read ten pages and threw it across the room.\" He called blog comments that responded to Cross' writing \"very entertaining,\" but also concluded, \"I don't care what any of my friends \u2013 or, for that matter, enemies \u2013 does to pay the bills. [...] I think my role in this is finished, so it's up to someone else to mention your massive cash donations to Operation Rescue, or your upcoming tour with Toby Keith.\"<ref name = \"Oswalt\"/>\n\nWhen it came to responses from professional writers towards Cross' behavior in the debacle, Jeff Bergstrom of ''[[BrooklynVegan]]'' opined that \"no explanation was needed; a person needs work. And to be honest, I found his 5 part response to be a mega-invaluable resource for learning what Cross has been up to these days.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Bergstrom |first=Jeff|date=January 4, 2008|url=http://www.brooklynvegan.com/cross-patton-th/|title=David, Patton, Theodore|website=[[BrooklynVegan]]|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Gawker]]'' stated the post \"will effectively quash any burgeoning feud between two of our favorite comedians\u2014especially since Cross demonstrated the above-referenced respect for his Pixar-blessed peer by not noting Oswalt's longtime involvement in ''[[King of Queens]]''.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Mark|date=January 2, 2008|url=https://gawker.com/339816/david-cross-explains-the-soul-searching-that-accompanied-cashing-his-alvin-and-the-chipmunks-paycheck|title=David Cross Explains The Soul-Searching That Accompanied Cashing His 'Alvin and the Chipmunks' Paycheck|website=[[Gawker]]|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref> C. Robert Cargill, on the other hand, thought that while Cross gave \"pretty good reasons\" in his post, \"he forgot that he could drop some really biting sarcasm in the place of a 1000-word diatribe\" and \"lost\" in responding to Oswalt.<ref>{{cite web|last=Robert Cargill|first=C.|date=January 11, 2008|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2758177/comedian-david-cross-and-the-great-chipmunk-debacle/|title=Comedian David Cross And The Great Chipmunk Debacle |website=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref> \n\n''Playlist'' was very harsh, calling Cross' post an \"extremely lengthy and tedious defense\" and that \"at least Jason Lee had the good sense to take the pay check and shut the fuck up.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Perez|first=Rodrigo|date=January 3, 2008|url=https://theplaylist.net/david-cross-defends-participation-in-20080103/|title=David Cross Defends Participation In Wretched 'Alvin And The Chipmunks' Film|website=The Playlist|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''The A.V. Club'', Steve Hyden called Cross' blog post a \"snide, dishonest, and largely unsuccessful attempt\" to deflect the harsh responses thrown at him. He cited similar public statements Cross made when involved in previous projects, such as when he discussed being in the ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'' episode \"[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent (season 6)|Bombshell]]\" with ''[[Time Out Chicago]]''; he elaborated, \"Even at his funniest Cross is distant, cold, untouchable; he either can't admit to the occasional lame moment in his own life or he honestly believes he's above the foibles the rest of us idiots are guilty of every day.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Hyden|first=Steven|date=January 2, 2008|url=https://www.avclub.com/david-cross-i-havent-worked-in-six-months-defense-1798213007|title=David Cross' \"I haven't worked in six months!\" defense|work=The A.V. Club|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n \nA week after Cross published on his blog, ''The New York Observer'' interviewed him and reported that he \"seemed genuinely hurt by the criticism he was being subjected to online.\" Cross stated while being interviewed:<ref name = \"Observer\"/>\n{{quote|There\u2019s no small part of people wanting to call you on your shit. And I think some of it\u2019s deserved on my part, but I also think a lot of it isn\u2019t. I think a lot of it is lazy and not really thoughtful. Look, do I really think that Lobsterboy103 thinks that I\u2019m \u2018evil\u2019? Of course not \u2026 But it\u2019s just the Internet, you know. It\u2019s tippity-tappity-tippity-tap \u2026 [here he mimics simian typing] \u2026 Done. Hit send.}}\n\nIn 2014, ''[[Flavorwire]]'' named Oswalt's snide remark in the MySpace blog the 30th harshest comedian-on-comedian insult of all time.<ref>{{cite web|last=Herman|first=Alison|date=August 27, 2014|url=https://www.flavorwire.com/474476/the-30-harshest-comedian-on-comedian-insults-in-history|title=The 30 Harshest Comedian-on-Comedian Insults in History|work=[[Flavorwire]]|accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards and accolades ===\nFox submitted ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' to the [[Academy Awards]] for a [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]] before the film had a theatrical run required for the award;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/39184-12-animated-features-submitted-for-oscar-consideration|title=12 Animated Features Submitted for Oscar Consideration|website=ComingSoon.net|date=November 8, 2007|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref> it wasn't nominated. Upon the announcement of the submitted films, Brad Brevet of ComingSoon.net question the submission of a live-action/animated film like ''Alvin'': \"I mean, why wouldn\u2019t ''Transformers'' then be considered animated?\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Brevet|first=Brad|date=November 1, 2007|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/521525-2008_oscars_the_animated_oscar_quandary|title=2008 Oscars: The Animated Oscar Quandary|website=ComingSoon.net|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref> While the [[Movieguide Awards]] named ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' the third best family film of 2007,<ref>{{cite web|last=Garcia|first=Elena|date=February 14, 2008|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/top-10-movies-of-2007-announced-at-christian-oscars.html|title=Top 10 Movies of 2007 Announced at 'Christian Oscars'|work=[[The Christian Post]]|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> ''[[PopMatters]]'' called it the second worst film of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/super-duper-bad-the-worst-films-of-2007-2496187805.html|title=Super Duper Bad: The Worst Films of 2007|work=[[PopMatters]]|date=January 10, 2008|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> It was also named one of 2007's worst pictures by science fiction writer [[John Varley (author)|John Varley]].<ref>{{cite web|authorlink=John Varley (author)|last=Varley|first=John|url=http://www.varley.net/Movies/Best%20&%20Worst%20of%202007.htm|title=Varley's Best and Worst Films of 2007|year=2008|website=Varley.net|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> In 2011, ''Entertainment Weekly'' ranked ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' the third worst live-action/animation hybrid film of all-time.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Lisa|last1=Schwarzbaum|last2=Gleiberman|first2=Owen|date=April 1, 2011|url=https://ew.com/gallery/5-best-and-5-worst-live-actionanimation-hybrid-movies/?slide=344691#344691|title=5 Best -- and 5 Worst -- Live-Action/Animation Hybrid Movies|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> In terms of lists regarding the worst talking animal films of all time, both ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' and ''[[Screen Rant]]'' named it eleventh worst.<ref>{{cite web|last=Striga|first=Danijel|date=December 17, 2015|url=https://screenrant.com/worst-movies-talking-animals/|title=11 Worst Movies Starring Talking Animals|website=[[Screen Rant]]|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Barone|first=Matt|date=March 30, 2011|url=https://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2011/03/15-most-obnoxious-movie-animals/alvin-and-the-chipmunks|title=The 15 Most Obnoxious Movie Animals|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> In 2013, it was ranked by ''[[GamesRadar]]'' the 48th worst Christmas movie ever.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kinnear|first=Simon|date=December 9, 2013|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/100-worst-christmas-movies/|title=100 Worst Christmas Movies|work=[[GamesRadar]]|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> In 2016, ''Box Office Prophets'' ranked it the fifth worst live-action film based on a cartoon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeprophets.com/column/index.cfm?columnID=18340|title=A-List: Worst Live Action Movies based on Cartoons|website=Box Office Prophets|date=April 14, 2016|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> The film also won a [[2008 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Award]] for Favorite Movie, a BMI Film & TV Award for Film Music, and was nominated for a [[Young Artist Award]] for Best Family Feature Film (Fantasy or Musical).\n=== Box office ===\n''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' was released in North America on December 14, 2007. The film grossed $44.3 million in 3,475 theaters its opening weekend averaging to about $12,750 per venue, and placing second at the box office behind ''[[I Am Legend (film)|I Am Legend]]''.<ref name=\"bom\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=weekend&id=alvinandthechipmunks.htm |title=Alvin and the Chipmunks (2007) - Weekend Box Office Results |accessdate=December 16, 2007 |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref> Its second weekend was $28.2 million, behind ''[[National Treasure: Book of Secrets]]'' and ''I Am Legend''. On its third weekend, it surpassed ''I Am Legend'' for #2 at the box office, but still ranked behind ''National Treasure: Book of Secrets''. The film closed on Thursday June 5, 2008, making $217.3 million in the US and $144 million overseas for a total of $361.3 million worldwide.<ref name=\"bom\"/> The sustained box-office success surprised [[20th Century Fox]]; Elizabeth Gabler of Fox 2000 told the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', \"I look at the numbers every day, and we just laugh.\"<ref name=\"horn\">\"[http://articles.latimes.com/2008/jan/03/entertainment/et-word3 'Alvin's' broad appeal pays off]\" ''Los Angeles Times'', January 3, 2008.</ref> Given its $60 million budget, ''Alvin'' was far more profitable than either ''I Am Legend'' or ''National Treasure: Book of Secrets''.<ref name=\"horn\"/> According to [[MTV]], it also became the highest-grossing talking animal/cartoon adaptation until its sequel. It is also 20th Century Fox's highest-grossing film in the US to be released in 2007.<ref name=\"mtv\">{{cite web | work=MTV Movie Blog | title=Alvin & The Chipmunks To Meet Chipettes in Sequel? | url=http://moviesblog.mtv.com/2008/01/09/alvin-the-chipmunks-to-meet-chipettes-in-sequel/| accessdate=January 18, 2008| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115074715/http://moviesblog.mtv.com/2008/01/09/alvin-the-chipmunks-to-meet-chipettes-in-sequel/| archivedate= January 15, 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n== Home media ==\n''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' was released on [[DVD]] in North America, Greece, and Mexico on April 1, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-DVD/699/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks DVD Release Date April 1, 2008|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-DVD/110126/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks DVD Release Date April 1, 2008 (Canada)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-DVD/89824/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks DVD Release Date April 1, 2008 (Alvin y las Ardillas) (Mexico)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Alvin-And-The-Chipmunks-Blu-ray/42014/|title=Alvin And The Chipmunks Blu-ray Release Date April 1, 2008 (\u039f \u0386\u03bb\u03b2\u03b9\u03bd \u039a\u03b1\u03b9 \u0397 \u03a0\u03b1\u03c1\u03ad\u03b1 \u03a4\u03bf\u03c5) (Greece)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Hong Kong on April 10, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-DVD/182237/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks DVD Release Date April 10, 2008 (Hong Kong)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> the United Kingdom on April 14, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-DVD/39635/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks DVD Release Date April 14, 2008 (United Kingdom)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> and Taiwan on November 24, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-DVD/182290/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks DVD Release Date November 24, 2008 (Taiwan)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> On [[Blu-ray]], the film was issued in the United States on April 1, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-Blu-ray/707/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks Blu-ray Release Date April 1, 2008|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Portugal, South Africa, and the United Kingdom on April 14, 2008,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-Blu-ray/3170/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks Blu-ray Release Date April 14, 2008 (United Kingdom)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-Blu-ray/76358/|ti