VD Release Date May 13, 2016 (Taiwan)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> and the United States on February 7, 2017;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-The-Chipmunks-4-Movie-Collection-DVD/131967/|title=Alvin and The Chipmunks 4 Movie Collection DVD Release Date February 7, 2017 (Alvin and The Chipmunks / The Squeakquel / Chipwrecked / The Road Chip)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> and as an iTunes collection on March 4, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/itunes/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-4-Movie-Collection-iTunes/18129/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks: 4-Movie Collection iTunes Release Date March 4, 2016|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNot counting releases that include sequels, Fox released three three-film sets in the United States that included ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'': a ''Kids and Family'' Blu-ray set that also featured ''[[Ice Age (2002 film)|Ice Age]]'' (2002) and ''[[Night at the Museum]]'' (2008), released on June 24, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Blu-ray-Kids-and-Family-Bundle-Blu-ray/31174/|title=Blu-ray Kids and Family Bundle Blu-ray Release Date June 24, 2008 (Ice Age / Alvin and the Chipmunks / Night at the Museum)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> a ''Family 3-Pack'' where ''Alvin'' came with ''Ice Age'' and its sequel, ''[[Ice Age: The Meltdown|The Meltdown]]'' (2006), released to Blu-ray on November 18, 2008;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Family-3-Pack-Blu-ray/1762/|title=Family 3-Pack Blu-ray Release Date November 18, 2008 (Alvin And The Chipmunks / Ice Age / Ice Age 2: The Meltdown)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> and a ''Triple Feature'' DVD where ''Alvin'' came with ''[[Flicka]]'' (2006), and ''[[Space Chimps]]'' (2008) released on April 6, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-and-Flicka-and-Space-Chimps-DVD/67385/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks / Flicka / Space Chimps DVD Release Date April 6, 2010 (Triple Feature)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Fox also issued a Blu-ray collection featuring ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'', ''[[Marmaduke (film)|Marmaduke]]'' (2010), and ''[[Home Alone]]'' (1990).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Alvin-and-the-Chipmunks-and-Marmaduke-and-Home-Alone-Blu-ray/55088/|title=Alvin and the Chipmunks / Marmaduke / Home Alone Blu-ray (Australia)|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> On March 30, 2018, Fox released an iTunes Store collection featuring ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'', ''Ice Age'', ''[[Horton Hears a Who! (film)|Horton Hears a Who!]]'' (2008), ''[[Rio (2011 film)|Rio]]'' (2011), and ''[[The Book of Life (2014 film)|The Book of Life]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/itunes/Fox-Family-Favorites-5-Movie-Collection-iTunes/98734/|title=Fox Family Favorites 5-Movie Collection iTunes Release Date March 30, 2018|website=Blu-ray.com|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Alvin and the Chipmunks: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Alvin and the Chipmunks|The Chipmunks]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|2007|11|20}}\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[Hip hop music|hip hop]], [[Dance music|dance]], [[Christmas music|Christmas]]\n| length     = 48:17\n| label      = [[Razor & Tie]]\n| producer   = [[Ali Dee Theodore]]\n| prev_title = [[Little Alvin and the Mini-Munks#Soundtrack|Little Alvin and the Mini-Munks]]\n| prev_year  = 2004\n| next_title = [[Christmas with The Chipmunks (2008 reissue)]]\n| next_year  = 2008\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = ''Alvin and the Chipmunks: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack Sampler''\n | type    = [[Soundtrack]]\n | cover   =\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = \n}}\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack was released November 20, 2007, three weeks before the film's opening and contains new versions of old songs such as \"Witch Doctor\" and \"The Chipmunk Song (Christmas, Don't Be Late)\" (as made famous by [[Ross Bagdasarian, Sr.|David Seville]] and [[Alvin and the Chipmunks|The Chipmunks]]), cover versions of songs such as \"Bad Day\" (as made famous by [[Daniel Powter]]) and \"Funkytown\" (as made famous by [[Lipps Inc.]]) and new songs such as \"Coast 2 Coast\", \"Get You Goin'\" and \"Get Munk'd\". The second track on the album is \"The Chipmunk Song (Christmas Don't Be Late)\", a remake version, without [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] as the voice of Dave. However, the seventh track, the rock version of the song, features Lee as the voice of Dave. The soundtrack is the first album to be released in three years by Bagdasarian Productions, and is the group's 43rd album overall. Four songs from the album have charted on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].\n\nThe album has been certified [[RIAA Certification|Platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] for shipments of over one million copies.\n\n===Reception===\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n|rev1score = {{rating|2|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1217153}}</ref>\n}}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->\nIn December 2007, the album debuted at #133 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. In its second week of sales, however, the album jumped to #67 on the chart.\n\nThe album's highest peak was #5 on the ''Billboard'' 200, making it the group's highest on the chart album since ''[[Chipmunks in Low Places]]'' (which peaked at #21). Following ''Alvin and the Chipmunk''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s DVD release, the soundtrack went back into the top ten from number 16 to number five with a 111% sales increase; it sold 51,000 copies of what was its 18th week on the chart,<ref>{{cite web|last=Hasty|first=Katie|date=April 9, 2008|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045912/strait-speeds-past-rem-to-debut-at-no-1|title=Strait Speeds Past R.E.M. To Debut At No. 1|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref> and was the issue's greatest gainer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045891/chart-shakers|title=Chart Shakers|work=Billboard|date=April 10, 2008|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\nThe album has been certified Platinum by the [[RIAA]] and has sold over 1,000,000 copies in the [[United States]]. By doing this, the album has become the group's first RIAA-certified album since ''[[Chipmunks in Low Places]]'' (which also went Platinum). ''Alvin and the Chipmunks: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack'' has become the Chipmunks' third Platinum album and sixth RIAA-certified album total.\n\n===Songs===\nFour songs from the album managed to chart on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 during the month of December 2007. By doing this, it became the group's first charting songs in 47 years (\"[[Alvin for President]]\" became the last charting single for the group; it peaked at #95 in 1960). Despite this feat, none of the songs were released as singles or ever solicited to mainstream radio (although it is possible that kid-oriented radio stations, such as [[Radio Disney]], might have played them anyway) and charted solely because of high digital downloads caused by the anticipation of the group's film, ''Alvin and the Chipmunks''.\n\nThe four songs that charted on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 (and with the chart peaks included and the songs' Hot Digital Songs peaks) were:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Song\n!align=\"left\"|Chart\n!align=\"left\"|Position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Witch Doctor (2007 Version)\" (featuring Chris Classic)\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"4\"|[[United States|US]] ''Billboard'' Hot 100\n!align=\"left\"|62\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"The Chipmunk Song (Christmas Don't Be Late) (2007 Version)\"\n!align=\"left\"|66\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Bad Day\"\n!align=\"left\"|67\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Funkytown\" \n!align=\"left\"|86\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Witch Doctor (2007 Version)\" (featuring Chris Classic)\n|align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\"|US [[Hot Digital Songs]]\n!align=\"left\"|16\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"The Chipmunk Song (Christmas Don't Be Late) (2007 Version)\"\n!align=\"left\"|28\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Bad Day\"\n!align=\"left\"|51\n|}\n\n===Track listing===\nA soundtrack sampler was released along with the DVD of the film in a two pack sold exclusively at Walmart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://reviews.walmart.com/1336/9185976/alvin-and-the-chipmunks-2007-with-soundtrack-sampler-cd-full-frame-widescreen-reviews/reviews.htm|title=Customer Reviews|publisher=Walmart}}</ref> This features five songs produced exclusively for the soundtrack.\n{{tracklist\n| headline         = Track listing<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Alvin-Chipmunks-Original-Picture-Soundtrack/dp/B000YK5BZU Alvin And The Chipmunks - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack], Amazon.com</ref> All songs performed by [[Alvin and the Chipmunks|The Chipmunks]] except noted\n| extra_column     = Performing Artist(s)\n| title1           = [[Bad Day (Daniel Powter song)|Bad Day]]\n| length1          = 3:47\n| writer1          = [[Daniel Powter]]\n| title2           = [[The Chipmunk Song (Christmas Don't Be Late)]] DeeTown OG Mix\n| writer2          = [[Ross Bagdasarian, Sr.|Ross Bagdasarian]]\n| length2          = 2:34\n| title3           = Follow Me Now (featuring [[Jason Gleed]]<sup>1</sup>) \n| writer3          = [[Ali Dee Theodore|The DeeTown Syndicate for DeeTown Entertainment, Inc.]]\n| length3          = 3:07\n| title4           = How We Roll\"<sup>1</sup>\n| writer4          = The DeeTown Syndicate for DeeTown Entertainment, Inc.\n| length4          = 3:54\n| title5           = [[Witch Doctor (song)|Witch Doctor]] (featuring Chris Classic)\n| writer5          = Ross Bagdasarian\n| length5          = 3:03\n| title6           = Come Get It 