sarian, Sr.]] \u2014 piano on track 15, the singing voice of Dave on track 15, and the spoken voice of Dave, as well as singing voices for Alvin, Simon, and Theodore on track 16\n*Aaron Sandlofer \u2014keyboards, bass, guitar, drums & uncharacterized backing vocals\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2007)\n!Peak<br />position\n!Certification\n!Sales\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|United States [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|align=\"center\"|Platinum<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/riaa/index.jsp Billboard.com - Find Music Business News Reports and RIAA Ratings<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1,000,000+\n|}\n\n====Score album====\nThe film's original score was composed and conducted by [[Christopher Lennertz]], a fan of the Chipmunks since childhood.<ref>\"A Note From The Composer,\" liner notes, score album, La-La Land Records LLLCD 1077</ref> La-La Land Records released a limited edition album on September 19, 2008.\n#Main Title (1:07)\n#I'm Late (:40)\n#Ever? (2:07)\n#Dave's Theme (:48)\n#No More Nuts/Storing Food for the Winter (4:43)\n#Rescue the Gear/Toaster Waffles (1:44)\n#Leave Me Alone (2:17)\n#I'll Clean Out My Office (1:35)\n#Are You Awake? (1:13)\n#Christmas Morning (4:09)\n#Live with Uncle Ian (2:36)\n#Dinner! (2:07)\n#Dave Remembers/Missing the Boys (1:08)\n#Get Them! (1:03)\n#Dave's Phone Call (1:06)\n#Theodore's Nightmare (1:05)\n#I Want to Go Home (1:28)\n#Alvin!!!/You'll Never Take Us Alive (4:09)\n\n==Marketing==\n\n===Video game===\n{{main article|Alvin and the Chipmunks (video game)}}\nThe video game for this film was released December 4, 2007 for the [[Wii]], [[Nintendo DS]], [[PlayStation 2]], and the [[Personal computer|PC]]. It was written and produced by DeeTown Entertainment.\n\n==Sequels==\n{{main article|Alvin and the Chipmunks in film#Live-action/animated films}}\nA sequel, titled ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]'', was released on December 23, 2009. [[Zachary Levi]] joined the cast to replace [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] due to his small role and because of his role on ''[[My Name Is Earl]]''; the main cast members reprised their roles for the sequel and the film also re-introduced [[the Chipettes]]. A third film, titled ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]'', was released on December 16, 2011. A fourth film, titled ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip]]'', was released on December 18, 2015.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0952640|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n* {{tcmdb title|664892|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n* {{bcdb title|94777|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n* {{Allmovie title|387020|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n* {{mojo title|alvinandthechipmunks|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|1184827-alvin_and_the_chipmunks|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n* {{metacritic film|alvin-and-the-chipmunks|Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n\n{{Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n{{Tim Hill}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alvin And The Chipmunks}}\n[[Category:2007 films]]\n[[Category:2007 soundtracks]]\n[[Category:2000s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2000s musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:American Christmas films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:American musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Alvin and the Chipmunks albums]]\n[[Category:Alvin and the Chipmunks films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Films shot in California]]\n[[Category:Live-action films based on animated series]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox films]]\n[[Category:Regency Enterprises films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tim Hill]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Christopher Lennertz]]\n", "name_user": "181.208.150.104", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alvin_and_the_Chipmunks_(film)"}
