e energies, imbuing allies with power and harming enemies. || ''Player's Handbook 2'' <ref>[http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/4dnd/20080815]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090726082959/http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd%2F4dnd%2F20080815 |date=July 26, 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Druid (Dungeons & Dragons)|Druid]]<ref>[http://www.gleemax.com/Comms/Pages/Communities/BlogPost.aspx?blogpostid=52842&pagemode=2&blogid=2132]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNtc4sJTdWc|title=GRZ - Mike Mearls at D&D Game Day 08|date=June 13, 2008|publisher=[[YouTube]]|access-date=December 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160418073543/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNtc4sJTdWc|archive-date=April 18, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> || Controller<ref>[http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/drfe/20081201a]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081203231631/http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd%2Fdrfe%2F20081201a |date=December 3, 2008 }}</ref> || Leader or Striker || Primal || Druids control powerful flora and fauna to attack at long range. They also transform themselves into agents of primal power, such as bears, monkeys, wolves, cheetahs, boars, treants, etc. || ''Player's Handbook 2''\n|-\n| Invoker<ref name=\"FinchAvengerInvoker\"/><ref name=InvokerPreview>{{Cite web |url=http://archive.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd%2F4dnd%2F20080815 |title=Archived copy |access-date=November 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20141111012915/http://archive.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/4dnd/20080815 |archive-date=November 11, 2014 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> || Controller<ref name=InvokerPreview /> || Leader or Striker<ref name=InvokerPreview /> || Divine<ref name=InvokerPreview /> || The Invoker channels the divine magic of their gods directly to castigate their foes and control the battlefield. They wear light to medium armor and can